left class=m><span class=title> Inking with G-pen ?</span><hr size=1> Hi, I am new to this board. I like drawing manga, I ussually draw them with pencil. And colour it with color  pencil. But lately I wanted to scan my work and colour it using photoshop, pencil don't come out to good with scanner. Soon I discover that you have to ink your work. So I took up my rotring and start inking.<br>
<br>
The thing with rotring is that It's very difficult for me to adjust the line width. Its much easier to do with pencil.<br>
<br>
So I went around looking at the web, and found out something about G-pen. This is first time I heard of it. Manga artist supposedly used this for their work. Anybody here uses G-pen ? Would you recommend it ? Is it troublesome to use ? (I was thinking about it dripping and all).<br>
<br>
An insight to this pen would be appriciated<br>
<br>
vfkidz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urtagent5.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rtagent5</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/29/01 12:32:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Inking with G-pen ?</span><hr size=1> Im sorry I dont know what a g-pen is, I use sukura microns and tomba brush pens<br>
<br>
