<br>
Remember, G pens are just a brand, and they come in all different types and sizes, just like Hunts and Speedballs do.  I've only owned one, it was a turnip pen, which is what we call a spoon in the States.  The only reason I bought that G pen in the first place was because that's all they had when I was stationed in Korea.<br>
<br>
I couldn't tell the difference between the two, personally.  That's why I get so confused when I hear folks raving about G pens, and how since that's what they use to ink manga in Japan, that's what you need to use!<br>
<br>
